<p style="line-height:1.295;margin-bottom:8pt;margin-top:0pt;" dir="ltr"><span style="background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-family:Poppins,sans-serif;font-size:13pt;"><span style="font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;">Technology has become an incredible ally in creating safer, more convenient homes for aging adults. Voice-activated systems, such as smart speakers, can control lights, thermostats, and even locks, eliminating the need to get up unnecessarily. Smart doorbells equipped with cameras allow you to see and communicate with visitors without opening the door, offering added security.</span></span></p>
